/*
:name: adv_div_by_zero
:type: error
:error: (divi|zero|nil|illegal)
*/
// Division by a literal zero is a bad operation: it must emit a diagnostic
// (the op yields nil; a nil in a constprop output should be reported), not
// silently fold. Today it folds with no error.
// (:error: regex is a placeholder — align to the real diagnostic.)
const x = 1 / 0
cputs("x")
